hopobject.name: Page
hopobject.body: Have you seen any good films recently? amitriptyline cream pain Alan Opie’s experienced Balstrode had depth, if less vocal power than in former years, and apart from Pamela Armstrong’s ordinary Ellen Orford, the line-up was strong – Pamela Helen Stephen (Auntie), Brindley Sherratt (Swallow), Jean Rigby (Mrs Sedley) and Jonathan Veira (Hobson) were all especially vivid. With their scores disguised as hymnbooks, the excellent chorus (London Voices) had self-righteous presence, and putting everyone in contemporary dress lent further claustrophobia – while probably causing mass cancellations of Suffolk weekend holidays.
